manifest.name: array-differ
manifest.description: Create an array with values that are present in the first input array but not additional ones
manifest.readme:
# array-differ [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/array-differ.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/array-differ)

> Create an array with values that are present in the first input array but not additional ones


## Install

```
$ npm install array-differ
```


## Usage

```js
const arrayDiffer = require('array-differ');

arrayDiffer([2, 3, 4], [3, 50]);
//=> [2, 4]
```

## API

### arrayDiffer(input, ...values)

Returns a new array.

#### input

Type: `unknown[]`

#### values

Type: `unknown[]`

Arrays of values to exclude.
